==English==

===Etymology===
[[blood]] + [[-y]]  (See Wikipedia[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloody] for discussion of etymology.)

===Adjective===
'''bloody''' (''comparative'' '''bloodier''', ''superlative'' '''bloodiest''', except for sense 3)

#Covered in [[blood]].
#:''All that remained of his right hand after the accident was a bloody stump.''
#Characterised by great [[bloodshed]].
#:''There have been bloody battles between the two tribes.''
#(''British, Australian, Singaporean mildly vulgar''; ''not [[comparable]]'') Used to intensify what follows this adjective.
#:'''1994:''' [[w:Robert Jordan|Robert Jordan]], ''Lord of Chaos'', 519 - Try to keep those '''bloody''' women's '''bloody''' heads on their '''bloody''' shoulders by somehow helping them make this whole mad impossible scheme actually work

